OL,6,F"No one," he said, "has been
OL,7,Funaffected by that night."
OL,9,FThe defendants argued in evidence that
OL,10,FMr Rogers was completing a training
OL,11,Fexercise, something he did regularly
OL,12,Fat the leisure centre.
OL,14,FWhile completing those exercises, the
OL,15,Fcourt heard that he often held his
OL,16,Fbreath as part of the training.
